### ============================================================
### HOW TO USE THESE .HTTP TEST FILES
### ============================================================
###
### SETUP:
### 1. Install the "REST Client" extension in VS Code (Huachao Mao)
### 2. Open any .http file and click "Send Request" above each ###
###
### GETTING A TOKEN (run these in order):
###
###   Step 1 — Send OTP to your phone (in auth.http)
###             POST /auth/send-otp
###
###   Step 2 — Verify OTP to get access + refresh tokens (in auth.http)
###             POST /auth/verify-otp
###
###   Step 3 — Copy the "access_token" from the response
###             Paste it into @accessToken = ... at the top of each file
###
### FILE OVERVIEW:
###
###   auth.http        — OTP login, profile setup, token refresh, logout
###   orders.http      — Create/list/cancel orders, courier order actions
###   wallets.http     — Check balance, top-up, courier payout requests
###   payments.http    — Card payments (Paylink), wallet payments, history
###   promocodes.http  — Apply promo codes, list active codes (public)
###   chat.http        — Conversations, messages, media, order images
###   couriers.http    — Toggle availability, list couriers by city
###   events.http      — Customer important events (CRUD)
###
### TEST CATEGORIES:
###   [SUCCESS]        — Happy path, expect 2xx response
###   [FAIL — Security] — Auth/authz tests: missing token, IDOR, forged JWT
###   [FAIL — Validation] — Bad input: wrong types, missing fields, out of range
###   [FAIL — Not Found]  — 404 tests for non-existent resources
###   [FAIL — Rate Limit] — 429 tests for rate-limited endpoints
###
### BASE URL: http://localhost:8000
### Change to your deployed URL if testing production.
### ============================================================

### Health Check — server is running
GET http://localhost:8000/health

###

### API Root
GET http://localhost:8000/
